#Problem APEX 5.5.11

## DBsubject(Calculus - single variable)
## DBchapter(Techniques of integration)
## DBsection(Approximation)
## Institution(Valdosta State University)
## Author(S. V. Ault)
## Level(3)
## TitleText1('APEX Calculus')
## AuthorText1('Hartman')
## EditionText1('3.0')
## Section1('5.5')
## Problem1('11')

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros('PGstandard.pl', 'PGML.pl', 'PGcourse.pl');

Context('Numeric');

$n = 4;

$c  = random(1, 9, 1);
$cs = $c**2;

$a = -$c;
$b = $c;

$f  = "\sqrt{$cs - x^2}";
$ff = Formula("sqrt($cs - x^2)");

$Deltax = ($b - $a) / $n;
$x0     = $a;
$x1     = $a + $Deltax;
$x2     = $a + 2 * $Deltax;
$x3     = $a + 3 * $Deltax;
$x4     = $a + 4 * $Deltax;

$y0 = $ff->eval(x => $x0);
$y1 = $ff->eval(x => $x1);
$y2 = $ff->eval(x => $x2);
$y3 = $ff->eval(x => $x3);
$y4 = $ff->eval(x => $x4);

$ans1 = ($Deltax / 2) * ($y0 + 2 * ($y1 + $y2 + $y3) + $y4);
$ans2 = ($Deltax / 3) * ($y0 + 4 * $y1 + 2 * $y2 + 4 * $y3 + $y4);
$ans3 = pi * $cs / 2;

BEGIN_PGML

[``` I =   \int_{[$a]}^{[$b]} [$f] \, dx```]

a) Approximate [`I`] with the Trapezoid Rule and [`n = [$n]`]. 

    [`I \approx \;`][_]{$ans1}{20}


b) Approximate [`I`] with Simpson's Rule and [`n = [$n]`].

    [`I \approx \;`][_]{$ans2}{20}

c) Find the exact value of the integral.

    [`I = \;`][_]{$ans3}{20}

END_PGML

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

[`\Delta x = \dfrac{b-a}{n} = \dfrac{[$b] - ([$a])}{4} = [$Deltax]`].
Find the values of [`x_i`] and [`f(x_i)`].

[```
  \begin{array}{l|l|l}
  i & x_i & y_i = f(x_i) = [$c] x_i^2 \\ \hline
  1 & [$x0] & [$y0] \\
  2 & [$x1] & [$y1] \\
  3 & [$x2] & [$y2] \\
  4 & [$x3] & [$y3] \\
  5 & [$x4] & [$y4]
  \end{array}
```]

a) Trapezoid Rule:

    [```
    \begin{aligned}
      T & = \dfrac{\Delta x}{2}\left[ y_1 + 2(y_2 + y_3 + y_4) + y_5\right] \\
      & = \dfrac{[$Deltax]}{2}\left[ [$y0] + 2([$y1] + [$y2] + [$y3]) + [$y4]\right] \\
      & = [$ans1]
      \end{aligned}
    ```]

b) Simpson's Rule:

    [```
    \begin{aligned}
      S & = \dfrac{\Delta x}{3}\left[ y_1 + 4y_2 + 2y_3 + 4y_4 + y_5\right]\\
      & = \dfrac{[$Deltax]}{3}\left[ [$y0] + 4([$y1]) + 2([$y2]) + 4([$y3]) + [$y4]\right] \\
      & = [$ans2]
      \end{aligned}
    ```]

c) The exact value is found using the Fundamental Theorem
of Calculus:

    [```
      \int_{[$a]}^{[$b]} [$f] \, dx =
      \left(\dfrac{[$c] x^3}{3}\right)\Big|_{[$a]}^{[$b]} =
      [$ans3].
    ```]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
